ulating the world and their multifarious interrelations. The papers collected in this volume dig into some of the intricacies presented by these problems. The papers here presented have been selected from those presented at the workshops bearing the very same name, “Causality and Motivation” organized in Bolzano and Rome.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCausation. 4aOntologie. 4aPhilosophie des Geistes. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPsychologie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh1 aAlbertazzi, Liliana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBello, Angela Ales, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroves, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacquette, Dale, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLove, Cyprian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManzotti, Riccardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoli, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoli, Roberto, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoy, Jean-Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeissman, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z978311033122608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook 